      number - The maximum number of items to return (between 1 and 100). Defaults to 10. (optional, default to 10)

    • searchMenuItems

      public SearchMenuItems200Response searchMenuItems(String query, BigDecimal minCalories, BigDecimal maxCalories, BigDecimal minCarbs, BigDecimal maxCarbs, BigDecimal minProtein, BigDecimal maxProtein, BigDecimal minFat, BigDecimal maxFat, Boolean addMenuItemInformation, Integer offset, Integer number) throws ApiException
      Search Menu Items Search over 115,000 menu items from over 800 fast food and chain restaurants. For example, McDonald's Big Mac or Starbucks Mocha.
      Parameters:
      query - The (natural language) search query. (optional)
      minCalories - The minimum amount of calories the menu item must have. (optional)
      maxCalories - The maximum amount of calories the menu item can have. (optional)
      minCarbs - The minimum amount of carbohydrates in grams the menu item must have. (optional)
      maxCarbs - The maximum amount of carbohydrates in grams the menu item can have. (optional)
      minProtein - The minimum amount of protein in grams the menu item must have. (optional)
      maxProtein - The maximum amount of protein in grams the menu item can have. (optional)
      minFat - The minimum amount of fat in grams the menu item must have. (optional)
      maxFat - The maximum amount of fat in grams the menu item can have. (optional)
      addMenuItemInformation - If set to true, you get more information about the menu items returned. (optional)
      offset - The number of results to skip (between 0 and 900). (optional)
